The paper focuses on fine-grained visual categorization and proposes a retrieval task for identifying unseen objects. This task involves using an incomplete auxiliary training set and a retrieval framework consisting of multiple components. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning a concise and discriminative representation using CN-Nets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves image retrieval and query expansion, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of a large-scale dataset and the need for identifying unseen objects suggest the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be relevant. Finally, the paper proposes a solution for large-scale fine-grained object identification, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
